  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime. While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty, the defendant has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. Considering the moderate amount involved and the lack of a criminal record, a sentence of 6 months, combined with a period of supervised probation and continued restitution, is sufficient to serve the interests of justice and rehabilitation without imposing an overly punitive sentence.",
  "verdict": 6
